<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/3(Thu) Scientifically Proven Differences Between Men And Women/ The Best Cities to Move To in 2020(host:Joyce)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=503&amp;p=525#p525"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">There is no on-site meeting on 6/3<br /><br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br /><br />Agenda:<br />07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks <br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation <br />8:00-8:40 pm Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation<br /></span>Session I:<br />Scientifically Proven Differences Between Men And Women<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.teddyfeed.com/health/men-and-women-differences/#:~:text=Scientifically%20Proven%20Differences%20Between%20Men%20And%20Women%201,it%20easier%20to%20get%20ou%20...%20%E6%9B%B4%E5%A4%9A%E7%BB%93%E6%9E%9C..">https://www.teddyfeed.com/health/men-an ... E6%9E%9C..</a><!-- m -->.<br /><br />1. Do you believe that men and women possess different skills? What are the gender stereotypes about men and women and their traits and skills?<br />2. Why are some jobs more suitable for men than women? Why are some jobs where women perform better?<br />3. Would you prefer to be a man or woman?<br />4. Who makes better leaders, women or men? Is there a gender difference in how men and women lead?<br />5. Do you prefer to work for a man or a woman?<br />Session II:<br />The Best Cities to Move To in 2020<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://goingglobaltv.com/the-best-cities-to-move-to-in-2020/">https://goingglobaltv.com/the-best-citi ... o-in-2020/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />For the second year in a row, Taipei claims the best city to live in. Almost all expats are satisfied with the local transportation, healthcare, Personal Safety, Tasty Food, Outdoors at Your Doorstep, Friendly People.<br />1. Have you ever considered moving to a new place to start over?<br />2. Where would you most like to live in the world and why?<br />3. How could such a tiny island-Taiwan be anybody’s favorite place to go?<br />4. How to make Taiwan a more welcoming environment for foreign professionals?<br />5. Language barrier is the most significant hurdle to working in Taiwan as a foreign national, what are the resolutions?<br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Fri May 28, 2021 4:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
